In Vue 2.x, [properties added to objects are not reactive](https://vuejs.org/v2/guide/reactivity.html#Change-Detection-Caveats). You have declared the `item` data item without the properties `Description` and `Price`, and have later assigned these properties using simple object assignment, which Vue will not be able to track.

There are two ways to solve this:

**[1. Declare all reactive properties upfront](https://vuejs.org/v2/guide/reactivity.html#Declaring-Reactive-Properties)**

Change `data` to
```javascript
data() {
    return {
      item: {
        Description: null,
        Price: null
      },
      parts: [],
    };
  },
```

**[2. Use Vue.set()](https://vuejs.org/v2/api/#Vue-set)**

Change
```javascript
this.item.Description = selectPart.Description;
this.item.Price = selectPart.Price;
```
to
```javascript
this.$set(this.item, &#39;Description&#39;, selectPart.Description);
this.$set(this.item, &#39;Price&#39;, selectPart.Price);
```

Thankfully [in Vue 3.x this caveat will be eliminated](https://medium.com/the-vue-point/plans-for-the-next-iteration-of-vue-js-777ffea6fabf) and all properties added to reactive objects will themselves become reactive.

Here is a more elegant solution to the problem. 

Replace .filter() with .find()

